The paper deals with adversarial attacks in computer vision tasks, specifically in the areas of robotics, face recognition, and autonomous vehicles. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also addresses the issue of safety in security-critical areas, which could fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for adversarial attacks, which could be of interest to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
